title: scenario
pid: d52ac119-c3c2-45db-a586-79d8f48cbc8f
body: |2-
  Imagine a process that checks for membership.
  It compares IDs (for people, say)
  from one data set to IDs in another,
  to see if the person is in the other data set.

  You build an algorithm. It's correct.
  It uses two lists of IDs.
